    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Electron micrographs demonstrating the subcellular localization of m2 receptor protein\"\n- \" Electron micrograph of a rare somatic synapse between an unlabeled axon terminal (a) and an m2-immunoreactive neuron (~2). Reaction product is not present postsynaptically but is plentiful outside the region of this synapse (arrows).\"\n- \"D, Junctional complex (arrow) binding two m2-immunoreactive dendrites. The junctional densities appear intensely immunoreactive.\"\n- \"F, m2-positive axon terminal (a) and preterminal axon (arrow). Synaptic vesicles appear to be surrounded by reaction product.\"\n\n- A junctional complex is not a synapse.\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Twelve young adult male Sprague-Dawley (Harlan) rats were deeply anesthetized ...\"",
